00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,700
 Well, the word repent itself means to turn.

260
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:14,140
 So if I'm repenting, if I'm walking this way,

261
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:16,940
 to repent would mean to turn around, right?

262
00:10:16,940 --> 00:10:18,800
 So that's what this young man is doing.

263
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,680
 He is turning around in his mind and his perspective,

264
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:24,060
 but then he also physically turns around.

265
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,280
 He returns to the Father.

266
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:30,580
 He leaves his foolish thinking and his foolish living,

267
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:33,980
 and he makes his way back to the Father.

268
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:38,700
 And what Jesus partially tells us this story

269
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,160
 so that we can get to this next part,

270
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,380
 about what happens next,

271
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:43,240
 when we would turn and we would repent,

272
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,460
 which is actually the reason I was so excited

273
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:47,280
 about preaching this specific sermon

274
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,120
 is for this next section.

275
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:53,500
 The son that repents and turns, what happens to him next?

276
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:57,900
 The story goes that, well, the Father does something crazy,

277
00:10:57,900 --> 00:11:00,900
 does something radical, something that is off script

278
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,420
 that no one would expect, right?

279
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:04,460
 The Father isn't reckless.

280
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:08,700
 The Father is responding to deep love.

281
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:10,260
 The Father is calculated.

282
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,660
 The actions of the Father

283
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:14,820
 are therefore interested in restoring.

284
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:15,660
 The text would say this,

285
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:18,100
 while he was a long way off, speaking of the son,

286
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:21,660
 his father saw him and was filled with compassion.

287
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:25,780
 He ran to his son, threw his arms around him and kissed him.

288
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:27,660
 The son said, "Father, I've sinned against heaven

289
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:28,500
 "and against you.

290
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:31,980
 "I'm no longer worthy to be called your son."

291
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,080
 But the Father said to his servants,

292
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:36,320
 "Quick, bring the best robe, put it on him.

293
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,500
 "Put a ring on his finger and sandals on his feet.

294
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,960
 "Bring the fattened calf and kill it.

295
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,440
 "Let's have a feast and celebrate,

296
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,620
 "for the son of mine was dead and is alive again.

297
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,140
 "He was lost and is now found."

298
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:49,340
 So they began to celebrate.

299
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:52,580
 The Father is overjoyed to see the son again.

300
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:55,140
 He doesn't wait for the son to make it all the way back.

301
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:57,340
 He says, while he was a long way off,

302
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:59,300
 the Father sprints toward him.

303
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:01,060
 The son's not even close to being home yet.

304
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:02,660
 The Father doesn't even meet him halfway.

305
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:04,700
 This idea that God's gonna meet us halfway

306
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,540
 is not biblical, right?

307
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:07,780
 Like, God goes the whole way.

308
00:12:07,780 --> 00:12:09,740
 Like, the son is all the way over there

309
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:11,580
 and the Father sees that he's turned around

310
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:14,020
 and is coming back and he runs towards him

311
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:18,860
 in compassion, overjoyed about this.

312
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:21,140
 And I think it gets me, what gets me is,

313
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,220
 when I try and visualize how beautiful this is,

314
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:25,560
 I think about my three-year-old son

315
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:28,140
 and how if there was a moment where he's coming to me,

316
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:30,300
 we used to live in Chonkwano

317
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,940
 and I used to get home from work late

318
00:12:31,940 --> 00:12:33,900
 and it'd be around maybe like seven or something

319
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,780
 and my wife would leave our estate

320
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:38,180
 and start walking towards us and I'd be walking home.

321
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:40,040
 And the second I saw my son,

322
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:43,340
 I mean, I didn't physically run because it's hot in Hong Kong

323
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:46,820
 but my heart ran, I was thrilled, I was so excited.

324
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:48,020
 I could only imagine, you know,

325
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:50,320
 when I've not seen my son for a whole day,

326
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,060
 this dude's son has been in a different country.

327
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:55,600
 The condition and the appearance of the son is saddening,

328
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,440
 probably breaks his heart.

329
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:00,640
 So it probably pushes him even more into that moment

330
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:03,600
 but the father runs to him, drops everything

331
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:07,540
 and is filled with compassion to see his boy again.

332
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:14,720
 This is a decisive and aggressive, fervent love.

333
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,600
 It's extreme grace.

334
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,120
 And it's extreme grace because note this,

335
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,240
 the father could have just forgiven him.

336
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,580
 This would have been a beautiful parable

337
00:13:22,580 --> 00:13:25,100
 if it was about how a son really messed up,

338
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:28,020
 I mean, as bad as it gets and he gets what he deserves

339
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:30,380
 and when he comes and tries to apologize,

340
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:33,340
 the father says, "Okay, you're forgiven."

341
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:34,180
 And that's the end of the parable.

342
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:35,540
 If that was the story,

343
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:37,980
 that would be a pretty powerful parable.

344
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:41,140
 But it doesn't just stop there.

345
00:13:41,140 --> 00:13:44,100
 The father's love is so extreme.

346
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:47,140
 It's so extreme that the son tries to get out his phrase,

347
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:49,500
 "Father, I've sinned against heaven and against you.

348
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,400
 I'm no longer worthy."

349
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,040
 And I imagine the father just putting his hand

350
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,300
 to his son's mouth, saying, "Stop.

351
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,280
 You're my son.

352
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:58,760
 You're here.

353
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,160
 That's what matters."

354
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:03,000
 And the father doesn't just forgive him.

355
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,800
 The father reinstates him.

356
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,640
 Rather than saying, "All is forgiven.

357
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,240
 Your slate is clean."

358
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:11,600
 The father says, "Go get the best stuff we have.

359
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,280
 Get the best robe," he says.

360
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:17,980
 "Get a ring, get a sandal, kill the A5 Wagyu."

361
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,560
 Like he wants the good stuff for his son,

362
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:24,080
 who has just done all this mess.

363
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,760
 He does not just forgive us.

364
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,520
 He reinstates.

365
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:31,080
 And I think we have to come to the understanding

366
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,660
 that this is God's posture.

367
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:35,640
 This is the father's posture to us as well.

368
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,420
 Can we talk about how,

369
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:42,320
 if I put myself in the position of the son,

370
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,960
 forgiveness would have been great.

371
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:47,980
 But I wonder how he felt when his dad hugged him

372
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:48,820
 in that moment.

373
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,700
 I wonder what he felt when he's dirty and stinky

374
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:55,780
 and smelly and tired and exhausted and not worthy,

375
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:58,780
 yet his father throws his arms around him.

376
00:14:58,780 --> 00:15:01,700
 Talk about getting more than you deserve.

377
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:02,980
 I feel like that motion probably,

378
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:07,460
 that moment probably flooded him with plenty of emotion

379
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:10,720
 to be received again.

380
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:14,620
 See, the father had no intention

381
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:16,740
 of making a repentant son a slave.

382
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:19,100
 I think we have to hear that for what it's really saying.

383
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:21,700
 Our father has no intention

384
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:24,180
 of making a repentant us a slave,

385
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:26,940
 but rather in his great joy,

386
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:30,420
 he restores us back to sonship and daughtership.

387
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,940
 It is joy that he does it.

388
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:33,380
 It's not because he has to,

389
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:35,460
 because he's God, because he's obligated.

390
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:36,460
 It's within his joy.

391
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:37,340
 And if you don't believe me,

392
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,700
 three different times it says it.

393
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,540
 In the first parable about the sheep,

394
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,740
 it says this, at the very end of it,

395
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:44,100
 he goes, "Rejoice with me.

396
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,420
 "I have found my lost sheep."

397
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:47,820
 When the parable gets to the next part about the coin,

398
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,100
 the woman says, "Rejoice with me.

399
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,420
 "I found my lost coin."

400
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:52,020
 When it gets to the son for the third time,

401
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:54,700
 "Rejoice and celebrate, be glad."

402
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:58,440
 There is joy that God feels about restoring you.

403
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:03,180
 When you come back, it is in his joy to bring you,

404
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:06,800
 not just to forgive you, but to reinstate you,

405
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:10,100
 to bring you into the family of God.

406
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,420
 Because in that space,

407
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:13,900
 there is a relationship that is restored.

408
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,780
 In that space, there is hope, there is meaning,

409
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:18,580
 there is identity.

410
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:20,960
 He wants to provide all of that for us.

411
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:24,220
 This restored identity is a theme

412
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:26,860
 that we cannot afford to overlook.

413
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:29,440
 There's something to be said about how identity

414
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:33,560
 and relationship are major threads into this story,

415
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,580
 and into the kingdom of God as a whole.

416
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:37,420
 I think that's why this story

417
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:39,580
 is drenched with identity imagery.

418
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:41,460
 Did you notice how every main character

419
00:16:41,460 --> 00:16:43,060
 isn't referred to by their name?

420
00:16:44,020 --> 00:16:45,700
 Or by their job?

421
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:49,500
 It's the father, it's the son, it's the other son.

422
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:55,980
 Who they are communicated as is based off of relationship.

423
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:57,700
 Relationship is so important.

424
00:16:57,700 --> 00:17:00,140
 It elevates the meaning of this parable.

425
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,300
 Let me think about it this way.

426
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,620
 What if this parable wasn't called the prodigal son?

427
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:05,720
 What if it was called the prodigal friend?

428
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:09,660
 You guys know Jethro, who leads worship here,

429
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:11,620
 stunning young man with the guitar.

430
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:13,060
 He's a good friend of mine.

431
00:17:13,060 --> 00:17:17,020
 If Jethro took my money and went to Indonesia,

432
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:21,340
 love you Jethro, and spent it all,

433
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:23,540
 and got what he deserved, lost his money,

434
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:26,260
 and is eating pig food, comes back to Hong Kong,

435
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:28,240
 and is like, bro, I'm sorry.

436
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,740
 Okay, well, first of all, I'm a pastor,

437
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:33,140
 so I'm gonna say yes, Jethro, I forgive you, right?

438
00:17:33,140 --> 00:17:35,280
 That's what pastors and Christians do.

439
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:41,380
 But if my son, Elias, made the same mistake,

440
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:45,300
 hear this, it would hurt significantly more.

441
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,140
 It really would.

442
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,440
 It would tear me apart.

443
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:53,100
 But if he came back, that joy would be ridiculous,

444
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:56,220
 and I would not stop at saying, you're forgiven, son.

445
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:57,040
 I'll go do your thing.

446
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,300
 You're forgiven, come be a servant.

447
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:01,860
 No, I would throw my arms around him, 'cause he's my boy.

448
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:04,460
 He's my kid, he's me, right?

449
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:06,620
 And I think if you understand this story,

450
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:08,580
 you understand the power of family,

451
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:10,140
 that's what Jesus is talking about.

452
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:12,680
 It's not just about the forgiveness of the sin,

453
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:16,140
 it's about the ultimate goal being restoring us

454
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:17,300
 into the right identity.

455
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:19,900
 The scriptures talk about this all over the place.

456
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,780
 Why do you think it is that we're called sons and daughters

457
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:24,300
 of God, children of God?

458
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:26,720
 When Jesus would teach the disciples to pray,

459
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,820
 which I find very fascinating,

460
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:30,580
 the one thing they tell him is, teach us this.

461
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:32,620
 They could tell him, they could ask him, teach us anything.

462
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:34,140
 He says, teach us how to pray.

463
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:36,540
 So Jesus says, okay, fine, I'll teach you how to pray.

464
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:39,180
 At that time, their posture towards divinity

465
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:41,940
 was that God is holy, God is Yahweh,

466
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:44,220
 we gotta be careful, make sure we don't sin too much,

467
00:18:44,220 --> 00:18:45,140
 go through all these rituals.

468
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:49,560
 And he says, when you pray, pray like this.

469
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:52,740
 Our father, relationship.

470
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:56,660
 Not our extreme maker who is bigger than everything

471
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:59,500
 or Elohim or our father.

472
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,780
 There is something so significant

473
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:05,980
 in this relationship identity concept

474
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:07,420
 that the scripture wants us to understand,

475
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,580
 and it's because of this.

476
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:12,580
 As children of God, we get certain perks.

477
00:19:12,580 --> 00:19:14,980
 There are things that happen within the family

478
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:17,380
 that won't happen outside the family.

479
00:19:17,380 --> 00:19:19,140
 The way I love my son would be inappropriate

480
00:19:19,140 --> 00:19:21,980
 for me to love any other person that way.

481
00:19:21,980 --> 00:19:24,340
 The way I love my spouse or my daughter

482
00:19:24,340 --> 00:19:25,180
 would be very different

483
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:26,700
 than the way I'm gonna love my friends,

484
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,220
 or the way I'm gonna engage with my friends.

485
00:19:28,220 --> 00:19:30,540
 See, when you're in the family, there's something different.

486
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:32,260
 There's a grace that's for the family,

487
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:34,260
 there's a certain compassion that's for the family.

488
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:37,000
 The family deeply matters.

489
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:40,100
 And I think about how my son, although he's three,

490
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,740
 and let me just say, I overestimated three, y'all.

491
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:46,340
 He is, whoo, he's perfect, but man, I'm stressing.

492
00:19:46,340 --> 00:19:48,460
 He does a lot of stuff, and I can never,

493
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:50,420
 I can't think of a reason that I would never love him.

494
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:52,460
 Like, I would love him no matter what.

495
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:55,520
 Like, he's great, but he's three, but he's great.

496
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:58,380
 But then there's you guys who, I like you,

497
00:19:58,380 --> 00:20:00,420
 but I'm sure there are things you can do

498
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:02,740
 to make me stop liking you real quick.

499
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:04,100
 All right, some of you don't have to try that hard.

500
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,140
 It's pretty easy for some.

501
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:09,140
 But not with my kid, not with my family.

502
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:11,480
 And God has this posture towards us.

503
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:13,620
 That's why the ultimate blessing,

504
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:16,140
 the ultimate thing we can receive is not a gift,

505
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,780
 a Ferrari or a better job

506
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:19,660
 or a more stable relationship at home.

507
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:21,140
 The ultimate gift we can get

508
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:22,900
 is to be brought back into his family.

509
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,240
 That's what Emma was talking about.

510
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:27,440
 By the blood of Jesus, we're not just forgiven,

511
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,560
 we're brought into his family.

512
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:33,540
 This is how God intended humanity to be.

513
00:20:33,540 --> 00:20:37,060
 In relationship with him, heirs of his,

514
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:41,020
 made to be like him, protected by him, his children.

515
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,660
 This is why Jesus in John three

516
00:20:42,660 --> 00:20:45,160
 would speak to Nicodemus at night and he would say,

517
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:50,920
 "You must be, you must be born again.

