00:31:40,340 --> 00:31:41,660
 We don't wanna be those kinds of people.

778
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:43,300
 I don't want us to be those kind of people.

779
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:46,360
 Our proximity to Christ isn't a badge we wear

780
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,300
 that makes us better than other people.

781
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:52,640
 It's not.

782
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,740
 It's not our permission to point and say,

783
00:31:55,740 --> 00:31:57,540
 look how bad they're doing.

784
00:31:57,540 --> 00:32:01,260
 Doesn't give us a right to get online

785
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:02,780
 and blast everyone that's not a Christian

786
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:04,540
 for the ridiculous things that they might do.

787
00:32:04,540 --> 00:32:06,260
 Guess what, they're not Christians.

788
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,100
 Imagine that.

789
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:13,140
 No, our proximity to God is meant to draw us close to him

790
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:15,260
 so that we can be transformed by him.

791
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:18,880
 Being close to God is less about being holier than others.

792
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:22,120
 It's more about becoming like him,

793
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:24,820
 becoming extreme in our grace,

794
00:32:24,820 --> 00:32:29,260
 choosing compassion over judgment,

795
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:30,700
 oozing with compassion.

796
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:32,120
 When our brothers and sisters are lost,

797
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:34,940
 being excited to see them come home,

798
00:32:34,940 --> 00:32:37,540
 co-laboring with the Father.

799
00:32:37,540 --> 00:32:39,700
 That's my heart for me, my family.

800
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:41,760
 That's my heart for us as a community.

801
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:43,540
 That in our weekly gatherings,

802
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:46,500
 in the gatherings that take place outside of Sundays here,

803
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:49,420
 that we would be growing in our likeness of God.

804
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:51,720
 That our hearts would be becoming softer

805
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:53,220
 and being more like his.

806
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:54,940
 That he would replace the heart of stone

807
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:55,960
 and give us a heart of flesh.

808
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:58,200
 That he would wipe away the scales from our eyes,

809
00:32:58,200 --> 00:33:01,420
 and we would see people the way that he sees them,

810
00:33:01,420 --> 00:33:02,900
 being shaped like him.

811
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:05,180
 That we would be broken for the loss,

812
00:33:05,180 --> 00:33:07,100
 the way that he's broken for the loss.

813
00:33:07,100 --> 00:33:10,000
 And that we would rejoice when they come home.

814
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,700
 We would rejoice when they repent.

815
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:16,780
 And for me, where I find this most challenging,

816
00:33:16,780 --> 00:33:18,260
 I have to ask myself this.

817
00:33:18,260 --> 00:33:23,260
 Would I be rejoicing, celebrating,

818
00:33:23,260 --> 00:33:25,460
 and the worst person that I know,

819
00:33:25,460 --> 00:33:27,240
 most filthy person that I know,

820
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,480
 the liar, the cheater,

821
00:33:29,580 --> 00:33:32,820
 the one who's weaseled their way, who's offended me,

822
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:35,100
 comes into God's family,

823
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:37,300
 and he gets the exact same privilege as I do.

824
00:33:37,300 --> 00:33:39,540
 Can I celebrate at that?

825
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:43,580
 Because I think it's that what drives the son crazy.

826
00:33:43,580 --> 00:33:45,100
 It's not just that he's forgiven.

827
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:48,140
 It's that he's now restored to the same level.

828
00:33:48,140 --> 00:33:49,760
 And that blood of Jesus, like Emma said,

829
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:51,860
 that is our ultimate equalizer.

830
00:33:51,860 --> 00:33:54,260
 That's what makes us all be able to be

831
00:33:54,260 --> 00:33:55,980
 on the same level again.

832
00:33:55,980 --> 00:33:58,220
 And that's what the father is ultimately showing us

833
00:33:58,220 --> 00:33:59,220
 through all of this.

834
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:03,160
 Now, with all this repentance and grace,

835
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,820
 I think there's one last question

836
00:34:04,820 --> 00:34:06,460
 that I want us to kind of wrestle with a little bit

837
00:34:06,460 --> 00:34:08,820
 before we get to a closing point.

